MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: (apps/client/src/shells/(pulse|vivid)/.+\.tsx?$|packages/game-cartridges/src/helpers/projections\.ts$)
MATCH_CONTENT: allPlayerResults
ADVISORY: |
  `allPlayerResults` is a PER-PLAYER signal, NOT a cartridge-completion signal.

  The async-game projection (arcade/trivia) emits `allPlayerResults` the
  moment the CALLING player's status flips to AWAITING_DECISION — by design,
  so ArcadeGameWrapper / GameLeaderboard can render the in-game leaderboard
  during the post-run retry screen (per ADR-126 §7).

  It does NOT mean the cartridge as a whole is done. For solo arcade, only
  YOUR run finished; the actor stays in `active` until ALL_COMPLETE or
  END_GAME. The cartridge actor only enters `completed` (final state) and
  output() runs when the LAST alive player submits.

  Do NOT use `if (c.allPlayerResults) → 'completed'` or equivalent. The
  legitimate completion signals are:
    - `thisCompleted` (entry in `completedCartridges` — written by L2 after
       output() fires)
    - `phase === 'COMPLETED' | 'REVEAL'` (only sync-decision cartridges
       expose top-level phase)

  Treating `allPlayerResults` as completion in the Pulse pill classifier
  caused a regression where solo arcade jumped to the result card instead
  of showing the score countdown / retry decision screen. Fixed in
  `659cb64` (apps/client/src/shells/pulse/hooks/usePillStates.ts).

  Same misread still exists at:
    - apps/client/src/shells/vivid/components/TodayTab.tsx:97
    - apps/client/src/shells/vivid/components/BroadcastBar.tsx:67

  Sweep them when convenient.
